column31: We want to share a little story with you.... "I take this every night before bed. I've struggled with hormone balance for awhile. I'm generally very busy and life can be very stressful (bet you guys can relate). This means I deal with chronically high cortisol levels and low progesterone. (Which means anxiety, inability to lose weight, disrupted sleep, occasional irregular cycles, breakouts, and more.) Awhile ago I got so tired of this I decided to try a natural progesterone cream, even though I normally don't agree with using hormones directly. I just wanted something to WORK. Well...it kind of did. It brought progesterone up and normalized my cycles, but didn't really lower cortisol and most issues didn't resolve. And when I initially tried going off it, my cortisol levels shot so high, I was jittery and couldn't sleep at all! Not worth it. I wasn't looking forward to withdrawal, so I decided to start taking this (pictured) again. No more withdrawal symptoms. Good sleep. Feeling calmer. With a few other minor changes (cutting out a few foods, more physical activity), I'm feeling much better. This really helps promote balance naturally." Can you relate to this?

column31: We already knew this, but here is a study ... Va((inated children are more likely to be diagnosed with developmental delays, asthma, and ear infections. I see it in many of my va((inated clients (babies, children and adults) - clinical science and observation from me for over a decade. A new peer-reviewed study by Hooker and Miller in the journal SAGE Open Medicine compares the health outcomes of va((inated versus unva((inated children from three large pediatric practices in the United States.The study concludes that unva((inated children are healthier than their va((inated peers. The researchers examined medical records for over 2000 children born between November 2005 and June 2015. The scientists followed the children continuously for a minimum of 3 years from birth. The research team determined each child’s va((ination status based on any va((ination received prior to one year of age. The unva((inated group represented 30.9% of the total. Results show that va((ination before one year of age led to significantly increased odds of medical diagnoses for developmental delays, asthma and ear infections. Read the full press release with links to the study at www.ChildrensHealthDefense.org.:=:https://childrenshealthdefense.org/ There are now over 60 va((inated/unva((inated studies on this site. All of them show dramatically better health in unva((inated children. We have found no studies that show superior health outcomes in vaccinated children. Via @robertfkennedyjr

column36:
For suspicion of forgery

A man was pressed down onto concrete with a solid 200 lbs sitting directly on his neck. He cried out for water. He cried out for his deceased mother, and once he realized he could no longer breathe, he cried out for mercy and he begged for his life. His nose bled and he lost control of his bladder. Yet he remained trapped and handcuffed under the weight of an officer’s knee.

Onlookers tried to intervene only to be threatened with pepper spray. Even when he lost consciousness, the weight of that knee stayed firm on his neck. When first responders demanded they check for a pulse, the cops refused. When off-duty medical personnel begged for the officer to get up, they refused.

America watched a man being killed in broad daylight for 10 agonizing minutes.

I understand people will dig through everything he’s done wrong in his life. I understand that people will roll their eyes at this. We will see his mug shot and he will become a villain even though surveillance video does not support police claims that he resisted arrest. But there is no crime that justifies this punishment. Whether he has a criminal history or mental health issues, there is no justification for his death.

His name was George Floyd

column31: Statistics show that nearly 40 million people in the United States will experience anxiety each year. And globally 1 in 13 suffer from anxiety. It seems the numbers grow more every year. Figuring out anxiety is not easy! It takes a lot of trial and error in order to find what really works for each person. Studies have shown links between low levels of several key nutrients and anxiety or depression. Checking for possible deficiencies, improving the quality of food you eat, and supplementing where necessary may decrease symptoms of anxiety. Herbs have also shown to be beneficial with anxiety. Cannabis, lemon balm, lavender, and others have beneficial effects on the nervous system, calming anxious feelings and making the body more capable of weathering stress. If you have ongoing anxiety, it’s best to talk to a naturopath or other natural health practitioner who can help you work through your specific needs. Looking at these nutrients and herbs is a great place to start. Study: Tumor Regression Stimulated by HBOT⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A non-randomized trial was conducted with 29 patients to evaluate the efficacy of radiotherapy combined with HBOT, in patients with a malignant glioma. Fifteen patients were irradiated daily after HBOT and fourteen other irradiated patients were treated without HBOT. In the HBOT group, 11 of 15 patients (73 percent) showed ≥ 50 percent tumor regression. In the non-HBOT group, only 4 of 14 patients (29 percent) underwent tumor regression. The median survival rate in patients with HBOT doubled that of the non-HBOT group (24 months vs. 12 months) respectively. No serious side-effects were observed in the HBOT patients. This provides additional support for HBOT to be a beneficial treatment for malignant gliomas. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column31: The coronavirus pandemic has negatively affected many people’s mental health and worsened symptoms for those already suffering from mental illness. A federal emergency hotline for people in emotional distress registered a more than 1,000 percent increase in April compared with the same time last year. Dozens of states and locally run distress hotlines have reported huge increases in call volume. Sales of alcohol are surging. Nearly half of Americans have reported a worsening of their mental health. This is frightening. Taking care of our mental health has never been more important. If you are feeling different, or notice a loved one is behaving differently, it may be time to get some help. Some symptoms to watch out for: -Feeling sad or down -Confused thinking -Low energy or problems sleeping -Excessive fears or worries, or extreme feelings of guilt -Mood changes of highs and lows -Withdrawal from friends and social events -Major changes in eating habits -Sex drive changes -Excessive anger or hostility -Suicidal thinking There are many different drug options available to treat these symptoms. These drugs may be necessary for people in very difficult situations. But they should be chosen only when truly necessary, used for a short period of time, and in conjunction with efforts to balance the body naturally. Side effects of anti-depressants are: -Feeling and being sick -Slight blurring of vision -Disorientation -Psychosis -Unconsciousness -Heart rhythm problems -Coma -Agitation -Seizures (fits) -Suicidal thoughts and a desire to self-harm Luckily, there are natural ways to help. A lot of times, mild depression symptoms can be a sign of a nutritional deficiency or hormonal imbalance, and supporting your body naturally with food and herbs can help you feel better. You don't have to spend your days fueled by pills. If drugs are not working for you, worsening your symptoms, or you just don't feel right taking them, you can go a more natural, safer route!

column35: Hear This Well
column36:
Lying by omission is the new "abundance of caution." This man couldn't lift his arm after the first dose, then felt more sick than he EVER HAD BEFORE IN HIS LIFE after the second dose. Despite having chills, a 103.2 fever, muscle aches, nausea, vomiting, and fainting, he proceeded to go on mainstream news to talk about the trial and never said one word about how sick it made him.

The people conducting the trial suggested his girlfriend call 911. 

Remember, you aren't entitled to know any of these details! He just happened to crack and tell STAT the truth.

"Haydon has spoken about the vaccine on CNN and CNBC. He even said he’d volunteer to be exposed to the novel coronavirus, SARS-CoV-2, if researchers want to test to see if the vaccine was actually effective. But up until now he has left out a key detail: He is, apparently, one of three people in the trial who had a systemic adverse reaction to the vaccine. 

Twelve hours after receiving his second dose, he developed a fever of more than 103 degrees, sought medical attention, and, after being released from an urgent care facility, fainted in his home. 

He has not brought up the side effects previously, he said, out of 'an abundance of caution.'

'I understand that sharing the story, it’s going to be frightening to some people,' he said. 'I hope that it doesn’t fuel any sort of general antagonism towards vaccines in general or towards even this vaccine.'

He said he received great medical care, and though he felt more sick than he ever has before, he was never afraid for his long-term health.

Given the stakes of a Covid-19 vaccine, the side effects described in the Moderna release would likely be seen as acceptable even if they turned out to be seen in future studies."

column31: Some people have been defending invasive contract tracing, lockdowns, and surveillance by saying "We've been doing it for a long time, look at Typhoid Mary!" Well. Let's just look at "Typhoid Mary," shall we? Her real name was Mary Mallon. She was an Irish immigrant who worked as a cook for several different households. She contracted salmonella typhi with mild symptoms, but unlike most people, she continued to shed the bacteria after she was well -- apparently, forever. Mary was the first known asymptomatic shedder, and no one knew what to do with her. So, they simply locked her up for two years. She attempted to sue the government for this, and lost. She was released, on the condition that she not go back to work as a cook -- which she did anyway. More people got sick, and she was again locked up, this time for the rest of her life. During her quarantine, no one took the time to explain to Mary WHY she needed to be careful, or how. They just told her "don't work as a cook." They did not explain to her that she was carrying a bacteria in her feces that, when she used the bathroom and didn't wash her hands, could easily spread to others. When they tried to control her and not treat her like a human, she rebelled. By the time Mary died, 400 other asymptomatic carriers had been discovered. None of them were ever quarantined or treated like Mary was, even though they had the same ability to spread disease that she had. Using Mary Mallon's situation to justify anything is justifying abuse. Plain and simple. The state was ethically and morally wrong. We should not be okay with what happened to her, and we should not want to repeat it now.

column31: There has been a debate between those who support mandatory lock-downs and those who do not for months, and those in support have chosen to frame it as the people who care about others, vs. those who are selfish. This is not, and has never been, accurate. We, and many others, have been raising the concerns in this article all along. There are *millions* of people who have been severely impacted by shut-downs in very serious, long-term ways. *Calls to suicide hotlines have increased 600% or more, and in some areas, they saw as many suicides in a 4 or 5 week period as in all of 2019. *Hundreds of small businesses have permanently gone under, meaning owners and employees will stay out of work (and these aren't "rich people" who can handle it easily, either). *Thousands of people have gone without medical care, because elective procedures and routine appointments were canceled, and/or they were afraid to go in. Many have already died because of it, and many more will. These are just a few of the devastating effects the shutdowns have had. This is HUMAN LIFE. To ignore these effects and shout "BUT COVID!" is to be purposely obtuse. To refuse to care about fellow man, while virtue signaling furiously. No one who has rationally opposed lock-downs has stated that we shouldn't be taking measures to support and protect the most vulnerable among us. But those who have supported shutdowns have said that non-COVID effects don't matter right now. You want to listen to the doctors, because they are the medical experts? Fine. column31: Where are my friends who love to be the best version of themselves, feel their absolute best and live their best life?! If you haven't jumped on the CBD bandwagon YET, my guess is because you’ve never tried it or used the right quality CBD and you may not even know why you’d want to. Let’s do a quick & valuable CBD 101. ✨CBD is short for cannabidiol. It works on the endocannabinoid system (ECS) in the body. The ECS’s job is to help the body maintain homeostasis or balance for all systems. You actually have endocannabinoid receptors all over your body to help modulate imbalance. Cannabidiol, better known as CBD, is a compound found in the cannabis plant. ✨ “Will CBD get me high?” No! YL’s CBD will not get you high. It’s an isolate, meaning it’s pure CBD, and 0.00% THC. Unlike tetrahydrocannabinol or THC, CBD does not get you high. ✨How is CBD made? CBD oil is made by extracting CBD from the cannabis plant. CO2 extraction removes the THC, leaving behind CBD. ✨Why use it? Not everyone makes {enough} endocannabinoids, due to endogenous and exogenous stress, poor diet, toxins, infections, etc... CBD has been shown to be helpful with everything from mood, focus, hormone balance, emotional elevation, optimal digestion, SLEEP and inflammation. CBD interacts with the body’s endocannabinoid system (ECS). A healthy, fully functioning ECS is essential in maintaining both physical and mental health. ✨Why YL when I can get it at the gas station? One word: QUALITY. Our CBD farm adheres to the same Seed to Seal standards as do all of our oils. No pesticides, fungicides, herbicides, heavy metals or solvents! ✨ YL’s CBD is “smart Spectrum”, meaning we combine the therapeutic properties of CBD with the terpenes in our essential oils for a synergistic effect, which in understandable terms means it's extremely effective for bringing any system that was out of balance..back in and very quickly and effectively. ✨What is the connection between ECS and my cannabinoid receptors? The ECS is made up of messengers also known as cannabinoids and two types of cannabinoid receptors, CB1 and CB2. CB1 receptors are located in the brain, connective tissue, gonads, glands, and organs. CB2 receptors are found in the digestive and immune system. 🌱🌿 What does this mean for ME? What this means is CBD has a supportive effect on the overall health of your body and brain. 👉 Think mental clarity, optimal memory, optimal digestion, positive mindset, modulated nervous system, a feeling of dancing with all of life's ups and downs - which we really can use with the state of the world.

column31: There are a lot of misconceptions about homeschooling. Many people believe that they don't have the time or aren't "qualified" to teach their children. Many work full time jobs, and think there's no way they could fit homeschooling into their schedule. We get it. It's overwhelming. But let's try looking at this with a different perspective. Firstly, lets discuss what the future of the public schools looks like... If and when public schools get back into session, our state is talking about implementing: *Spraying kids and their belongings with disinfectant at the gate *Keeping kids 6 ft. apart in classrooms and on the playground *No-contact activities (no gym, no assistance with lunches, no real play) *Masks *Gloves What kind of mental and physical impacts do you think would occur from this? Think about disruptions to the microbiome from daily disinfectant spraying, and lack of socialization or meaningful connection to other humans. Would you send your kids to school in this environment? We understand that homeschooling may not be ideal for everyone. However, when there's a will, there's a way! You don't need a strict schedule to home school. You can get creative and experiment to find a way to comfortably fit it into your weekly routine! Take a look at your weekly schedule, and figure out when it is that you have free time. If that's evenings and weekends for you, then take a couple hours in the evenings and on the weekends for homeschooling. Or if you work nights and weekends and have weekdays off, then set aside a couple hours during the day for school time. The number of hours you spend homeschooling your kids isn’t as important as what they are learning or how they are learning. Most home-schoolers don't work with their kids for 6+ hours a day, they only need an hour or two because there isn't classroom management or busywork, just one or two children so it goes much faster. We do understand that sometimes it's just not a possibility to home school, and that's okay! But if it's something you are considering, we fully support you and have some great resources to help you along the way!

column31: From RFK, Jr.: Heroic Easton Bans 5g. Three Cheers for Easton Connecticut, the first New England town to order Big Telecom to stop its 5G wireless rollout. On May 7, Easton’s Town Selectmen, in a bipartisan vote, unanimously approved a resolution ordering those companies to “cease and desist” their buildout of 5g infrastructure until research and testing proves it safe for humans and the environment. The American Academy of Pediatrics and hundreds of medical and scientific experts have advised the Federal Communications Commission to test the long-term safety of 5G technology. A $25 million FDA study in 2019 found “clear evidence of cancer and DNA damage” among myriad injuries known to be caused by 5g. The resolution presages a confrontation with the Telecom Titans. Should Telecom press forward, Easton can either deny or refuse to process applications. Easton’s famed 5th Regiment played key roles in turning back Imperial Redcoats at Lexington and Concord and in subsequent Revolutionary War battles. First Selectman Dr. David Bindelglass told me that he and his fellow lawmakers took the action solely due to overwhelming public demand. Please send an Email to Dr. Bindelglass (dbindelglass@eastonct.gov) to thank all the Selectmen, Republican and Democrats, for their courage against corporate tyranny.

column31: Alan Dershowitz is one of the most dangerous men in America. "Let me put it very clearly, you have no constitutional right to endanger the public and spread the disease, even if you disagree. You have no right not to be vaccinated, you have no right not to wear a mask, you have no right to open up your business. ...if you refuse to be vaccinated, the state has the power to literally take you to a doctor's office and plunge a needle into your arm. Public health, the police power of the Constitution gives the state the power to compel that.” Dershowitz literally says here that the state can use its police powers to forcibly vaccinate you. Here's what he doesn't understand. (Beyond that this is a HUGE violation of informed consent.) No one has the right to knowingly, purposely spread disease. If you know you are sick, and you cough on someone or spit on them, that is considered assault. And of course it is. But *inadvertently* exposing someone else to disease because you didn't know you were sick and you were performing normal activities, like breathing or touching public items, is not remotely the same thing. Any time you go out in public, you are accepting that others who are currently ill, or presymptomatic, might be there or have recently been there. You might get sick. You should wash your hands after returning home, or while you're there as well to reduce your risk. You have absolutely no right to "not be exposed" to illness ever. Further, vaccines are not foolproof. People can still contract and spread the illness even if they are vaccinated. Is it acceptable if you accidentally impact someone else if you're vaccinated, but not if you aren't? The end result is the same. This type of "logic" is flawed and very dangerous. These times we're living in are unprecedented. Pharma and its faithful followers must be taken down.

Remember when he gave the ZDogg interview describing what happened in the Filipino dengue vaccine nightmare with the "Antibody Dependent Enhancement" reaction that killed vaccinated kids when they were exposed to wild dengue? 

He explained that for vaccines, like coronaviruses, where scientists can't make proteins that look like the virus does in nature:

Binding antibodies = bad
Neutralizing antibodies = good

He said that vaccine makers must make sure that the quantity of NEUTRALIZING ANTIBODIES had better be far greater, and more persistent, than the binding antibodies. Or children will die.

And here it is, right in the Moderna press release: 

https://investors.modernatx.com/news-releases/news-release-details/moderna-announces-positive-interim-phase-1-data-its-mrna-vaccine

They have neutralizing antibody results for 8 of the 45 test subjects: 4 in the 25 microgram dose group (that's the lightest dose), and 4 in the 100 microgram dose group (that's the medium dose).

"The levels of neutralizing antibodies at day 43 were at or above levels generally seen in convalescent sera." Oh, OK. Great. That's wonderful news, right? The good little neutralizing antibodies were mostly equivalent to the levels that someone who overcame an infection had. Super.

But in the sentence just before that, "At day 43, two weeks following the second dose, at the 25 microgram dose level, levels of binding were at the levels seen in convalescent sera."

OK, what about the high dose group?

"At day 43, at the 100 microgram dose level, levels of binding antibodies SIGNIFICANTLY EXCEEDED the levels seen in convalescent sera."

WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON HERE? Why is this being paraded around like it's great news after Paul Offit just explained that outnumbering the neutralizing antibodies will end up with dead kids when they're exposed to the wild virus?

column31: There's an unfortunate narrative in our culture now that fighting for freedom is just selfishness in disguise. But this is completely wrong. "Freedom" doesn't mean for just one person or a small group of people. It doesn't mean that people get to do whatever they want with no consequences. It means that *everyone* gets to decide for themselves what is right, and that when there's conflict or disagreements, people work together to find the best outcome for all. (Convincing people that ‘freedom’ is selfish has led to people asking for their rights to be taken away!) No small group just gets to decide for everyone else or "be right." No one gets to force anyone else into doing something they don't want to do. Freedom is actually the opposite of selfishness, because it respects that there are many ways of being and most are perfectly fine. It lets each person be autonomous and respected. That's why we believe in it so strongly. To each his own, and voluntary community with mutual respect.

column36:
Over the past two decades, serving both as Deputy Coroner and Coroner, I, as well as the staff of my office have always made every attempt to be as straightforward and honest with the residents of this county and family members of every person we serve. 

During the ongoing COVID-19 crisis, it has been brought to my attention some untruths and misleading statistics released by the Department of Health. 

Last week, I placed many phone calls to the Department of Health in an attempt to correct these inconsistencies. I believe that the residents of our county should not be misled or confused by falsified data. Unfortunately, my calls fell upon deaf ears. 

The Department of Health and their website, which is updated daily, had reported that six people in our county had died due to COVID-19. This is incorrect. Where and how they came up with this number is unknown to me.  The correct number for Armstrong County is two. 

Over the weekend, my office subpoenaed the Dept. of Health to get information related to all the deaths they attributed to Armstrong County.   As of their noon website update, the number of Armstrong deaths had been corrected, and now reads two. 

As to their motives behind inflating the numbers, I haven’t a clue.  However, I am positive that other counties are in the same position. 

As a public servant and elected official, I believe in transparency and truth in numbers. The residents of Armstrong County should always be made aware of the truth.

column31: When do you B R E A K F A S T? 🤔 Did you know that delaying the hour of the first meal of the day can help you lose body fat & live longer...even if you change nothing else about your diet?! Personally, I used to eat within 1-2 hours of waking. I thougt I couldn’t possibly exercise or begin work w/o fuel in my system. It never occurred to me that I didn’t need to eat so early. Plus, it was simply my life-long habit. But in the past year or two, I’ve started what some call “time-restricted eating.” I’ve learned from experts I’ve interviewed on the Wise Traditions podcast (like @dr.tomcowan & @marisa_moon_ among others) that lengthening the time we fast overnight has innumerable benefits, including: ✅ improved mental focus ✅ better energy ✅ a break for the gut ✅ deeper sleep ✅ cellular detox ✅ fat loss & lengthened telomeres (as mentioned at the top) So now, most days, I have two goals in terms of the timing of meals: 1️⃣ eat only during daylight hours 2️⃣ break fast no earlier than 10 a.m. Crunching my eating window in this way often results in 14-16 hour overnight fasts. I feel terrific, rather than deprived, & more “on” in the mornings, whether working out or working.☺️ Oh, & when I DO eat, it feels decadent & nourishing—like you see here: picadillo tacos w/ feta cheese, fermented salsa, & farm fresh eggs on nixtamalized corn tortillas. 😋 Nutrient-density for the win!! And intermittent fasting for the win, too!! Yeah, it’s a real win/win! 👑 Have you tried crunching your eating window? I suggest you give it a go! You’ve got nothing to lose (save a little body fat😉)! P.S. Look for Wise Traditions podcast #223 “Why intermittent fasting?” 🎧 for more insights on this wise tradition!

This morning I discovered this post all over the place. 

A baby and a mother are at risk of being separated due to a nurse taking a postpartum mothers temperature before she was discharged while she was sleeping, established that it was too high for her comfort, whatever that means, and have now placed this mom in a situation where a mother and her baby are being held hostage like PRISONERS, being watched on a video camera full-time and refused to be discharged, all because the mother is refusing a COVID test. 

Instead of being able to bond with her baby and be at peace and feel safe to release her hormones to nurse and heal her body, she is now in a state of DISTRESS. This kind of behavior and disturbance of the postpartum hormones can lead to psychosis, depression, anxiety, even suicide. And not only are they traumatizing the mother, but the infant that feels every bit of their mothers distress. If they have this baby taken away from this mom, imagine the trauma they will cause to BOTH OF THEM. 

ALL. OVER. CORONAVIRUS. 

I want to know: 

Did this mother receive an epidural? As this increases the likelihood of a fever, that is not serious, but a normal physiological response to having medication in the body that the body is not used to. 

Did this mother receive an IV drip? This can also lead to her having a fever, as the body attempts to sweat out excess fluid. 

Perhaps we can consider the fact the this woman JUST GAVE BIRTH, in a HOSPITAL full of GERMS, and perhaps her body is doing what it should, flaring up her immune system to fight those germs and create antibodies. 

But we don’t think like science and logic when we are in media-led fear of a virus do we? 

Concord Hospital. you are a DISGRACE. Let this mother go and save yourself the additional lawsuit damages that are coming your way. 

Anyone in NH that is available needs to set up a protest at that hospital NOW. Call your local news stations, your governors, get everyone that you can involved. This is UNACCEPTABLE.

column31: According to FDA research, some of the active chemicals in sunscreen seep into our blood stream! Results of a small study showed that after applying sunscreen lotion, cream and spray, the chemicals Avobenzone, Oxybenzone, Octocrylene, and Ecamsule were found in the participant’s blood in just one day ― and at levels past the FDA guidelines! Oh but don't worry... Researchers "agreed" that the participants in the study applied more sunscreen than what the average person does. I'm sure these researchers know how often people apply sunscreen to themselves or their children throughout a hot summer day. I hope they took into consideration a day at the beach. Or summer sports that involve being outdoors all day long. Regardless, just knowing that these chemicals are absorbed into our bloodstream is enough to question the risks of applying it! If they're just now figuring this out, what else don't they know about the potential dangers of these chemicals? https://health.clevelandclinic.org/study-reveals-that-sunscreen-can-be-absorbed-in-the-bloodstream-but-dont-panic-yet/

column31: It’s getting W I L D out there! 🤪 Is it just me or do you feel it too? Tension is thick on social media & in real life. There is 🦠 fear of the virus 🦠 fear of each other 🦠 anger re. 😷 or no masks 🦠 anxiety about the future It makes me want to check out of civilization & go off grid. Since this isn’t in the cards just now, what do I do to ⬇️ anxiety & ⬆️ peace? I keep up my basic wellness rhythms so that the world’s beats don’t drive me batty. 🦇 Here’s a snapshot of my morning routine: ☀️morning sun - I get out between 30-45 minutes of sunrise. I gaze in the direction of the sun for 10-15 minutes. I do gentle movement & prayer at the same time. It sets my circadian rhythm, signals melatonin production, & sets the tone for my day. ☀️quiet time - I spend time journaling my thoughts, hopes, frustrations, etc. I also always include what I’m grateful for. Reminds me that there is PLENTY of good amidst it all. ☀️sweat - I work out (mix of cardio & strength training) 3x per week. I sweat in my sauna 3x per week. All of this happens BEFORE I get on my phone, check emails, or hear any news. By prioritizing nature, prayer, & movement, I establish a solid base so that I am steadier when the world tries to rock me. In a nutshell, this morning routine is my saving grace, tbh. 🙌 What does yours look like? (And let me know in the comments below if you’d like to hear what my end-of-the-day routine looks like too! ☺️) P.S. Go to my website & sign up for my blog for practical tips to ⬆️ health & sanity in these crazy times!

However, neither PCR nor antibody testing for SARS-CoV-2 is terribly reliable, and a significant proportion of affected children has tested negative on one or both. Why, therefore, have most researchers—along with the entire mainstream media—decided to go on record with their belief that the new pediatric syndrome is linked to COVID-19? column31: Have you ever heard of water kefir?! It’s a specific type of culture, a symbiotic relationship of bacteria and yeasts (like kombucha, but different strains). It's fizzy like soda, and has a pleasant taste. The strains in kefir may actually help re-colonize your gut, which so many people need these days! If you like fruit-flavored sodas, then you will LOVE this recipe! This strawberry lemonade natural soda is healthy, delicious, and perfect for Summer! Directions: Step 1: Mix all the ingredients in a quart-sized glass jar, until the sugar is dissolved. Put a lid on it and set it in a warm place (70 – 75 degrees). Step 2: Let this sit for 24 hours. Step 3: Strain the liquid into two 16-oz. bottles. Add 2 – 3 small strawberries to each bottle, plus half the lemon juice. Put the caps on tightly. Step 4: Re-start the water kefir as in step 1 (more water, sugar, and the water kefir grains — they should grow and will be good indefinitely as long as you use them regularly). Step 5: Let the bottled kefir sit on the counter for 1 – 2 days. Transfer to the fridge. When you are ready to enjoy, open over the sink, because it may be very bubbly and could make a mess! It’s simple, yummy, natural soda!

column31: First, we should state that we're firm supporters of medical freedom. Some people feel safest, for themselves, by getting vaccinated. Others feel safer *not* getting vaccinated. Unfortunately, not everyone feels that people should be able to make a choice. Some think that everyone ought to get vaccinated "for safety." But this is honestly a silly argument. If someone isn't vaccinated, and responsibly chooses to stay home when they are sick, the chances of them ever affecting anyone else are incredibly small. So very, very, very tiny. And if they do, chances are that the people affected will have a mild, acute illness and recover fully. Saying that people should "have" to vaccinate to protect others is basically like saying that people should never drive again. Every time you get behind the wheel of a car, you have a chance of getting in an accident. If you get distracted or look down at the wrong second...that's all it takes. And in fact, car accidents injure and kill FAR more people than illness ever did. While fewer than 10,000 people per year typically died of illnesses we now vaccinate for (at a time when medical science was a lot less advanced), 1.25 MILLION people die in car accidents, and 20 - 50 MILLION more are injured or disabled. So if it's really all about public safety...why not ban all driving?! That's not a rational solution to the problem, because of the benefits of driving, and neither is forcing people to vaccinate (due to ignored and critical injury statistics). What do you think?

column31: Aware friends, today, let's talk the Immune System and Molds. Having these assessed and cleared by a skilled root cause practitioner will be important for short and long terms healing. Our immune systems protect us from dangerous pathogens, like bacteria, including Lyme’s Borrelia burgdorferi, parasites, viruses, and fungi (including mold). It shields us from the harmful substances we encounter, including environmental toxins, heavy metals, biotoxins, and more. White blood cells, called lymphocytes, carry out adaptive immune responses. There are two broad classes of these responses: cell-mediated immune responses and antibody responses. They are carried out by different types of lymphocytes, called T cells and B cells, respectively. In the cell-mediated immune response, activated T cells take direct action against foreign antigens. T cells might kill an infected or toxic host cell. Or, the T cell might produce a signal molecule that activates macrophages which engulf and destroy invaders, toxins, and cellular debris. Activated B cells secrete antibodies–proteins called immunoglobulins. The antibodies circulate in the system, where they bind specifically to the foreign antigens, inactivating the mold biotoxins. As a result, the biotoxins can no longer bind to receptors on host cells. Mycotoxin exposure comes from ingestion, dermal transmission, and inhalation. Mold toxins are extremely potent and often affect nearly every organ system in the body. Some of the symptoms associated with Chronic Inflammatory Response Syndrome (CIRS) include: +Brain fog, memory issues, cognitive and focus difficulties +Mood swings +Digestive problems +Fatigue; weakness +Frequent urination; excessive thirst; dehydration +Weight gain +Muscle and joint pain +Blurry vision; light sensitivity +Postnasal drip; sore throat +Numbness; tingling +Tinnitus +Static shocks +Dizziness +Metallic taste in the mouth +Low-grade fever +Shortness of breath +Headache Key elements of the immune system which I bioscan assess for clients include: 📈 +Spleen Your spleen helps your body fight infection. Just as it quality checks red blood cells, your spleen can identify unwelcome pathogens in your blood. In conjunction with the lymph nodes, it creates an organized force of defender cells called lymphocytes. Lymphocytes are specific white blood cells that produce antibodies. +Lymph Nodes These are nodes, vessels, and tissues located throughout the body, including in the neck, armpits, abdomen, and groin. The lymph nodes help break down harmful germs. Also, they filter toxins for removal from the body in lymph fluid. White blood cells contained in the lymph nodes help fight infection. +Bone Marrow Bone marrow is the spongy tissue located inside some of the bones in the body, such as the hip and thigh bones. Bone marrow makes 200 billion new red blood cells every day.3 It also produces white blood cells and platelets. If the bone marrow isn’t functioning well and produces abnormal white blood cells, those cells may be unable to fight infection. +White Blood Cells The bone marrow produces white blood cells, or leukocytes. These are crucial for a healthy immune system. They fight and protect against infections. They are stored in the spleen, the bone marrow, and the lymph nodes. White blood cells can circulate throughout the body. They collect in areas where there is an infection. +Mycotoxins can significantly impair the antibody production of the adaptive immune system. column31: NEW Aluminum research--Abstract: A burgeoning number of studies are demonstrating aluminium in human brain tissue. While research has both quantified and imaged aluminium in human brain tissue in neurodegenerative and neurodevelopmental disease there are few similar data for brain tissue from non-neurologically impaired donors. We have used microwave assisted acid digestion and transversely heated graphite furnace atomic absorption spectrometry to measure aluminium in twenty brains from donors without recognisable neurodegenerative disease. The aluminium content of 191 tissue samples was invariably low with over 80% of tissues having an aluminium content below 1.0 μg/g dry weight of tissue. The data for these control tissues were compared with data (measured using identical procedures) for sporadic Alzheimer’s disease, familial Alzheimer’s disease, autism spectrum disorder and multiple sclerosis. Detailed statistical analyses showed that aluminium was significantly increased in each of these disease groups compared to control tissues. We have confirmed previous conclusions that the aluminium content of brain tissue in Alzheimer’s disease, autism spectrum disorder and multiple sclerosis is significantly elevated. Further research is required to understand the role played by high levels of aluminium in the aetiology of human neurodegenerative and neurodevelopmental disease. Full text available: https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-020-64734-6:=:https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-020-64734-6?error=cookies_not_supported&code=d44f4b5a-d444-45aa-912c-9a18eb4afd7e

column31: This week, the FDA gave the green light to Moderna to move ahead to phase two efficacy trials for its coronavirus vaccine even though the results of phase one safety trials aren't yet known. From the article: History provides plenty of reasons to be wary. In 1955, a hastily-approved polio vaccine contained live polio virus, which killed 10 children and created 200 cases of paralysis. In 1976, a swine flu vaccine created 10 cases of Guillain-Barré syndrome per million people vaccinated, killing 25 people. And occasionally, vaccines can create a more intense form of the illness they’re intended to protect against: In 2017, a vaccine against dengue fever was suspended in the Philippines, after it was discovered that, in rare cases, it increased the risk of severe infection among those who hadn’t been previously infected.

column31: Listen to Dr. Peter Hotez discussing "Immune Enhancement" which is a paradoxical phenomenon of the coronavirus vaccine, in which vaccinated people who do get infected develop a more severe form of the disease than people who have never been vaccinated. In studies of an experimental SARS vaccine reported in 2004, vaccinated ferrets developed damaging inflammation in their livers after being infected with the virus. The same thing also happened with feline coronavirus vaccines and human RSV vaccine. There’s a GOOD reason we don’t have a vaccine against #coronavirus "Potential vaccines should be tested in animals first" (but they’re not) "to rule out disease enhancement, before trials move on to humans." He says he "understands the reasoning for pushing SARS-CoV-2 vaccines to human tests quickly, but adds that, because of the possibility that a vaccine could enhance disease, “I’m not sure this is the vaccine you want to do it for”. Where there is risk, there must be choice. #informedconsent #covid #covid19 #covid_19 #covidvaccine #pandemic #healthfreedom #medicalfreedom

column36: 3 years ago today you weren’t yourself, you were really lethargic all day. I knew you really didn’t feel well because even when you were sick you usually would still be smiling and happy but I remember you really seamed out of it. Madeline just had gotten a new bed and we were sitting on it and I was reading you a book and I was about 30 seconds into it I turned around and you were passed out. You never fell asleep anywhere besides your crib or in your car seat when we are driving. I remember telling mommy and sending her this picture because you fell asleep so fast on Madi’s bed and it was not like you. I tried to wake you up after telling Mommy on the phone and you weren’t moving. I remember my heart dropped trying to shake you and wake you up finally you opened your eyes and looked at me. It really scared me. We were going to take you to the doctor in the morning but you woke up and seemed much better the next day smiling and playing again. Looking back you had the fevers on and off the rash from the shot right away, the crying at night, you puked one night in your bed and pediatrician would always say the fevers are normal. It’s not normal you were having a reaction to the shot. They tell you to take Tylenol but by doing that it actually depletes you glutathione which is needed to flush out all the toxins and garbage. So by giving you Tylenol we were actually making you weaker. 4 days later you went to bed and never woke up. After you passed we started looking back at all your records and pictures afterwards. You were always sick right after getting shots and we never put it all together. We trusted our pediatrician and she failed us. All about money. Makes me sick. I’ll never stop fighting for you Nicholas. You should be here i miss spending time with you. Hurts so much looking at these. Daddy loves you more than you will ever know Nicholas. Goodnight 💔✈️💙

column31: This is going to be controversial, but we think it needs to be discussed. Our society, right now, is all about what we should be doing "for others." We should be forced to get vaccines, wear masks, stay home...all for the benefit of other people. All to prevent spreading illness we likely don't even have. But there is NO discussion about how to protect the individual. We don't want to talk about what steps people can take (beyond the the usual hand washing) to actually protect themselves. It's true that people who choose healthy foods, exercise, practice stress reduction and mindfulness, and engage in other healthy behaviors, have a lower risk of illness than those who don't. Why can't we talk about this? Why don't we work to protect ourselves FIRST? Once we have done what we can to keep ourselves healthy, then we worry about our neighbors. This is not to say that healthy choices are a guarantee, or that we shouldn't respect other peoples' boundaries (for example, if someone is immunocompromised and wants you to wear a mask in their home or not visit right now, then respect that). But the conversation needs flipped. We talk about what we CAN control (ourselves) first; then what we can possibly do for each other. It promotes fear to focus on feeling worried that our neighbor won't take steps to protect us, while we can't do anything for ourselves. Let's stop promoting fear and a loss of control, and do what we can, first and foremost, to protect ourselves.

column31: Most people are used to seeing the FDA disclaimer on natural health websites and products: "These statements have not been evaluated by the FDA, and this product has not been proven to prevent, treat, or cure anything." It makes some people nervous. They wonder if the product is safe, if it can even do anything, or what is going on here! The truth is, the FDA does not regulate the supplement/natural health industry at all. (And most of us are happy about that! There are several third-party certifiers that don't have conflicts of interest that do a fine job.) But, they do look at label content, and insist that that disclaimer be present. It doesn't mean the product doesn't work. In fact, companies can have studies in hand showing that it does, and still can't make any claims, because that would make it an "unapproved drug." The presence of this disclaimer doesn't really mean anything other than the product is considered a supplement instead of a drug. And isn't that what we're all looking for?
column34: The "FDA disclaimer" is a legal statement, not medical one. Earthley -wellness

column31: Facebook, Google, and Microsoft are part of 31 tech companies that announced "the Open RAN Policy Coalition", a group that will lobby the U.S. government to increase competition in the tower hardware space. The Coalition is working to change the way cell tower radio access networks (RANs) work; they want multiple vendors’ “open” hardware and software so they can be used interchangeably rather than requiring one vendor’s proprietary “closed” products. The group wants the U.S. to fund the research and development, test interoperable solutions, and offer incentives to diversify the network supply chain. As the Coalition’s founding membership roster indicates, there’s no shortage of companies interested in getting more involved which will demand millions of tower radios globally in the 5G era alone. These companies want to find more ways to make even more profit but they want our taxpayer money to fund their "risk". Considering the financial power of these corporations, the US Congress is unlikely to resist.
column35: Open RAN Policy Coalition unites 31 tech companies to lobby U.S. on 5G

column31: Yeast rashes can be embarrassing and uncomfortable. Especially in the warmer months when you just want to wear a pair of shorts or slip on your sandals and not have to worry about a visible rash! Yeast is a common fungus that is floating around us all of the time. There are many different kinds of yeast. Candida is a kind of yeast that naturally lives in and on the body. It is harmless in small amounts, and actually helps to keep our digestive and immune system healthy! However, an overgrowth of yeast can cause an infection, and other health problems. A lot of people experience yeast rashes during warmer weather. This is because yeast will grow faster at higher temperatures. Sweating, humidity, and lack of ventilation can also cause a yeast overgrowth. Yeast rashes can occur on the skin, mouth, genitals, feet, and nails. These rashes are common, and some symptoms include; redness, sores, itching, burning, and swelling. Luckily, there are natural ways to deal with yeast rashes! Applying nourishing, anti-fungal oils such as; tea tree oil, neem oil, and coconut oil. Herbs like calendula, cloves, cinnamon, and garlic have anti-fungal and antibacterial properties. Probiotics, natural yogurt, and apple cider vinegar are other options to help repress yeast growth!

column31: Attention, Wisconsin Advocates! Here's a call to action from Wisconsin United for Freedom: There will be an Executive Hearing on Clearing House Rule 19-079 on Tuesday, May 5th at 11:00am at the state capitol room 411. CR 19-079 would add an additional vaccine to the required list of vaccines for school entry (the meningococcal vaccine). They state that "the evidence of its harmfulness is accumulating" and mention the WHO 2B "possible carcinogen" classification from 2011. They also quote the precautionary principle which is legally binding in Europe (not in the US). While this effort is welcome, considering the clear evidence of harm--not only scientific but also human--we are past the precautionary stage. We need action to stop this. A reminder, in March 2019, Brussels, Belgium, has become the FIRST city in the world to halt 5G due to health effects. The city's Environment minister said:"The people of Brussels are not guinea pigs whose health I can sell at a profit. We cannot leave anything to doubt " (To read about Brussels decision: https://www.brusselstimes.com/…/radiation-concerns-halt-br…/).

column31: Epidemics that began as human error: #scienceisunsettling People born between 1946 and 1964, called the baby boomers, comprise 25 percent of the US population (there were 74.1 million boomers in 2016). This generation has a higher rate of Hepatitis C compared to other generations. About 1 in 30 baby boomers is infected with Hepatitis C, which can lead to liver disease, cirrhosis of the liver and liver cancer. A study published in the Lancet looked for causes for this Hep C epidemic among the baby boomers, and found that the peak of hep c transmission occurred in 1950, when the oldest baby boomers were about 5 years old, and determined that "nosocomial or iatrogenic factors" (meaning medical care setting, i.e. reused medical equipment, syringes, etc. ) "RATHER than past sporadic behavioural risk" (i.e. risky behaviors such as IV drug use or unsafe sex) caused the epidemic. Reuse of needles and syringes in health care settings before disposables became the uniform standard of practice and is what spread hepatitis C in this generation of children. Disposable syringes became widely used after 1965, which is when this epidemic ended. Penicillin was made available to the general public in 1945. The DPT vaccine (diphtheria, pertussis, tetanus) was combined into a single shot in 1948. Sterilization was not up to par. https://www.bcmj.org/news/baby-boomers-risk-hepatitis-c:=:https://bcmj.org/news/baby-boomers-risk-hepatitis-c https://www.thelancet.com/journals/laninf/article/PIIS1473-3099(16)00124-9/fulltext https://circleofmamas.com/the-science-is-unsettling/

column31: Now that it's public information that the news and 'others' have completely inflated and LIED about the prevalence of COVID-19... let's get out and on with living life and supporting health and immunity. Excellent summary from my wonderful friend Jill Boman. Several great points here from Bill Maher (5 minute video), that are similar to some of my own wonderings about the psychological and cultural effects of this whole COVID circus and this new ultra sanitized life. NOTE: He does swear a few times in the video just as a heads up. 1. Life is for living (my paraphrase of Bill's "What's the point of life if you can't live it."), and living entails risk. To quote another opinion piece (link in comments): "It is supposed to be reassuring when various establishments inform me that “Your safety is our first concern.” Dear heaven above, I hope not! Excellence? Virtue? Yes. Development as a complete human being? Sure. But safety? Our first concern? Has our society become so pampered that we have forgotten we live in a world where risk is an intrinsic part of every moment of every life? Where tens of thousands of people die in car crashes every year? Where people trade years of life for an increased daily intake of sugar and salt?... All worthwhile activities always involve risk of death—to oneself and others. That is no excuse for assuming a fetal position and failing to live one’s life." 2. We will never win the war against microbes because: A. They are EVERYWHERE. 🦠🦠🦠 B. They are SO MUCH everywhere, we are essentially swimming in a sea of microbes, and always have been. You could even say that say WE are largely microbial: An estimated 90% of the cells that make up our bodies are microbial--all manner of bacteria, fungi, viruses (yes, viruses), and parasites form our own personal ecosystem. We are only 10% *us*, outnumbered 10 to 1 by microscopic life forms, but we would die without the symbiotic relationship we have ALWAYS had with the incredibly complex and integrated microbial world living within, on, and around us. If we don't make friends with this microbial world--if we continue to wage war against it and become successful--we will die along with the microbes that have been helping to keep us alive throughout all of human history. Even contracting an illness and going through the process of sickness and recovery is good for us--it strengthens our immune system the same way lifting weights strengthens our muscles. When used-to-be rite-of-passage childhood illnesses were common and not feared (ie. measles, mumps, chickenpox) parents and pediatricians often noted developmental leaps in children after recovery. A child who couldn't tie their shoe or ride a bike could suddenly do it! Somehow, overcoming the challenge resulted in an overall leap ahead in more ways than one. I worry about what young children are learning by observing the behavior of society (not to mention some of the horrible ideas I've seen about how to return kids to school in the fall!)--like Bill here mentions, are they doomed to an irrational fear of microbes? And are we causing them (and ourselves) to fear each other? In our heightened safety and sanitation consciousness are we ceasing to live? If this is the "New Normal" I keep hearing about, I don't want it for myself or for future generations. There is nothing healthy about it. “Governors should declare keeping our bodies in good health an essential job”. - Bill 5 Minute video: https://youtu.be/28I5WyLp15o:=:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=28I5WyLp15o&feature=youtu.be

column31: 1918: Spanish Flu The first cases of the influenza pandemic that would eventually make it around the globe, began in Haskell County, Kansas and at Camp Funston at Fort Riley, Kansas. A mess cook came down with “the flu” in March, and within 3 weeks over 1,000 soldiers were ill. The illness traveled with the military to Europe and beyond, eventually killing 50 million people, although subsequent autopsies would find that they died of secondary bacterial infections, and not influenza itself. Many doctors at the time did not think it was a flu but some kind of plague: it struck in the summer and fall (rather than winter), was most deadly in young people ages 20-40 (verses the young and the elderly), and had strange symptoms like projectile nose bleeds, coughing up blood or a sanguine foam, and turned a persons skin bluish black color, or sometimes spotted black (reminiscent of the pneumonic plague). Patients gave off a strange and puzzling stench. At the time BMJ wrote: “bacteriological examination... has revealed an organism described as parameningococcus”. In addition to typhoid (whole cell), smallpox (live), diphtheria antitoxin, tetanus antitoxin, in January 1918 the men at Fort Riley, Kansas were given several injections of a new experimental meningococcal vaccine developed by the Rockefeller Institute, grown in horses. Gene sequencing of the virus that allegedly caused the Spanish Flu revealed avian origin, but there are models that have speculated that the virus became virulent from a horse intermediary. “Transmission between horses and humans seems to have been key to some epidemics when horses were an intimate part of our lives,” says Richard Lenski, an evolutionary biologist at Michigan State University in East Lansing. “We now have this idea that the source for a lot of influenza virus we see now worldwide is potentially equine, whereas the dogma has been for so long that its avian.” Bottom line, the training camp was extremely overcrowded, and the men were given multiple injections with reusable syringes. Including a new, experimental anti-meningitis vaccine grown in horses at the Rockefeller Institute. https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/b382/66368819c1a916824e635c343f13fad3abf3.pdf #spanishflu #pandemic #scienceisunsettling #pandemics

column31: Outbreaks that started because of human error: #scienceisunsettling 1966, 1973 and 1978: Smallpox In 1973 Charles Rondle was conducting research on smallpox at the London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine, which ended up infecting lab technician Ann Algeo, and several more people, including patients at the hospital. The University of Birmingham Medical School in the United Kingdom had two smallpox outbreaks: The first occurred in 1966 when medical photographer contracted smallpox but was not diagnosed for 8 weeks and was not quarantined. A total of 12 further cases were identified. In 1978, also medical photographer: Janet Parker worked in the photo lab one floor above the school's research laboratory that was growing a smallpox strain. Despite being previously vaccinated, Janet Parker contracted smallpox and ultimately died. Her mother came down with smallpox but survived, and her father died of a heart attack shortly after visiting her in the hospital. The head of the University’s microbiological dept. committed suicide while in quarantine. In response to the exposure, 260 people were quarantined, over 500 people were given smallpox vaccinations. No further cases were identified. In 1978, The WHO was about to declare smallpox eradicated on a worldwide level, but because of the lab-caused outbreak, they had to wait until 1980. In 2014, the FDA moved to a new office, and left 100s of unclaimed vials of virus samples in a cardboard box in a cold storage room, 6 of which contained smallpox. Luckily it didn’t result in an outbreak, but human error is a reality. It happens more than we know. #pandemic #science #labs #smallpox #outbreak #quarantine #labaccident #wuhan #coronavirus #covid #covid19

column31: Outbreaks that started because of human error: #scienceisunsettling 1916: Polio H.V. Wyatt suggests that the polio epidemic of 1916 which began in Mid-May (well before summer which is more typical of polio transmission) in an Italian neighborhood of Brooklyn, NY was very likely accidental release of a virulent strain of polio virus from the Rockefeller Institute at 63rd Street and York Ave., just a few subway stops away from the Italian neighborhood in New York City. At the exact time of this outbreak, Simon Flexner at the Rockefeller Institute had been passaging spinal cord tissue containing poliovirus between Rhesus monkey spinal cord to another, because they had been unable to infect monkeys by feeding. This particular Rockefeller “MV” strain would only replicate in monkey neural cells, they would find in 1936 when Sabin tested the virus for several “ill-fated” vaccines. Subsequent study of the MV strain found that it caused polio. New York saw 8,900 cases of paralysis with 2,448 deaths, and in total 23,000 cases with 5,000 deaths throughout New England and the Eastern states. The exceptionally high case-fatality rate (higher than any other known outbreak) could be because the virus was made more virulent, or because of the treatments at the time, which may have included human and animal globulins, sera, lumbar punctures—all with unsterile solutions and medical equipment including reused syringes, needles and no protective equipment. Read more: https://benthamopen.com/contents/pdf/TOVACJ/TOVACJ-4-13.pdf Read about the medical treatments: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4293735/ #polio #poliovirus #poliooutbreak #pandemic #outbreak #covid #covid19 #publichealth #rockefeller #science #medicalscience

column35: Melissa
column36:
PAY. VERY. CLOSE. ATTENTION.

⁉️ Bill Gates wants us to build vaccine factories and make sure governments across the world—who are suffering extreme economic crisis—find a way to fund this process. For a virus with a 99.5-99.9% recovery rate, he wants at least 7 BILLION doses made for every single person on the planet. He says the new vaccine technology may not work, the safety may have serious problems, and it will likely only give you protection for a few months. 😳  So there will have to be annual Covid vaccines for the entire planet in order for us to go “back to normal”...
—————————

⚠️ From Bill Gates: “Now it’s looking like [RNA vaccines are] one of the most promising options for COVID.... There’s a catch, though: we don’t know for sure yet if RNA is a viable platform for vaccines.”

“[COVID vaccine] might not be a perfect vaccine yet—and that’s okay. The smallpox vaccine is the only vaccine that’s wiped an entire disease off the face of the earth, but it’s also pretty brutal to receive. A small—but not insignificant—number developed more serious reactions. The smallpox vaccine was far from perfect, but it got the job done. The COVID-19 vaccine might be similar.”

“We have a bit more wiggle room with efficacy. I suspect a vaccine that is at least 70 percent effective will be enough to stop the outbreak. A 60 percent effective vaccine is useable, but we might still see some localized outbreaks. Anything under 60 percent is unlikely to create enough herd immunity to stop the virus.”

“It’s possible we do something similar to the shingles vaccine [increasing the dose in the elderly] for COVID, although it might come with more side effects.”

“How long does it last? Ideally, the vaccine will give you long-lasting protection. But we might end up with one that only stops you from getting sick for a couple months (like the seasonal flu vaccine, which protects you for about six months).”

“Even if it isn’t [perfect], we will continue working to improve it. After that happens, I suspect the COVID-19 vaccine will become part of the routine newborn immunization schedule.”

“We need to manufacture and distribute at least 7 billion doses of the vaccine. In order to stop the pandemic, we need to make the vaccine available to almost every person on the planet.”

“What we can do now is build different kinds of vaccine factories to prepare. Governments need to quickly find a mechanism for making the funding for this available.”

“Most people agree that health workers should get the vaccine first. But who gets it next? Older people? Teachers? Workers in essential jobs? I think that low-income countries should be some of the first to receive it, because people will be at a much higher risk of dying in those places.”

“Eventually, though, we’re going to scale this thing up so that the vaccine is available to everyone. And then, we’ll be able to get back to normal...”

column31: Here's an interview with a technology journalist who's been covering telecommunications for 20 years. He says: "I think the lack of interest in 5G rests with the operators. They haven’t effectively explained why 5G is important, why people should care, and what it’s actually going to deliver. 5G is easily one of the most overhyped technologies I’ve covered in 20 years. It will become the standard eventually, but for now, there are just too many unproven proclamations about what it will actually enable." ".. I don’t view it as a revolutionary technology." In regard to the part they did explain he said: "I think some of these aspirations including peak speed, latency, high-speed handoffs, between sites and energy consumption will only be achieved in the lab or highly specialized environments." However, it seems that they were able to confuse the journalist as well as he completely missed the point - reduction of speed does not pay for $200 billion in infrastructure - what will be the data extracted - data which will be sold for surveillance and artificial intelligence.
